DNS - domain name system - used to resolve human-readable names (google.com) to ip addresses.
Machines such as PCs dont use names, they use ip addresses.

C:\Users\user>ipconfig /all

R1(config)#ip dns server
R1 (config)#ip host R1 192.168.0.1
R1 (config)#ip host PC1 192.168.0.101
R1 (config)#ip host PC2 192.168.0.102
R1 (config)#ip host PC3 192.168.0.103
R1 (config)#ip name-server 8.8.8.8
R1 (config)#ip domain lookup